"723","Putnam International Growth Fund"
"724","77E Legal Proceedings"
"725","In late 2003 and 2004, Putnam Management settled charges brought"
"726","by the SEC and the Massachusetts Securities"
"727","Division in connection with excessive short-term trading in"
"728","Putnam funds. In July 2011, the fund recorded a receivable"
"729","of $3,597,168 related to restitution amounts in connection with"
"730","a distribution plan approved by the SEC.  These allegations and"
"731","related matters have served as the general basis for certain"
"732","lawsuits, including purported class action lawsuits against"
"733","Putnam Management and, in a limited number of cases, some Putnam"
"734","funds. In May 2011, the fund received a payment of $161,045"
"735","related to settlement of those lawsuits. Putnam Management has"
"736","agreed to bear any costs incurred by the Putnam funds as a"
"737","result of these matters."
